review_blob: Pours dark reddish brown with a large offwhite head.  Nose is malt and nut.  Taste is roasted malt, caramel, chocolate, toffee, and spice.  Nice but not spectacular.
Pours amber with a huge, fizzy, offwhite head.  Nose is malt, bread, and citris.  Taste is malt, caramel, and spice.  A nice ESB.
Pours pale gold with a big white head.  Nose is malt and corn.  Taste is bread, grass, fruit, and spice.  The combination of flavors didnt mix well for me on this one.
Pours amber with a large, uneven offwhite head.  Nose is hops and citris, as is the taste.  Nice strong bitterness in the finish.  A good IPA.
beer_name: Flying Dog Snake Dog IPA (2008 and later)

review_blob: Pours amber with a large, uneven offwhite head.  Nose is hops and citris.  Taste is moderately hoppy, with notes of citris and grapefruit.  A decent IPA, but nothing spectaclar.
Pours amber with a small, fast diminishing head.  Nose is malt, caramel, pine, fruit and toffee. Taste is malt, grapefruit, and moderate hop bitterness.  A nice APA.
Pours dark brown with a small offwhite head.  Nose is malt, caramel, fruit, and toffee.  Taste is malt, nut, caramel, toffee and spice.  A nice seasonal.
Pours pale gold with a small white head.  Nose is malt, bread, and light hops.  Taste is malt, bisquit, and lemon.  Refreshing, but unremarkable.
Pours amber with a thin white head.  Nose is malt.  Taste is malt, bread, and caramel with medium hop bitterness. A good everyday beer.
Pours dark amber with a small offwhite head.  Nose is hops and pine.  Taste is malt, pine, grass, grapefruit, and moderate hop bitterness.  Pretty good stuff.
beer_name: Southern Star Pine Belt Pale Ale

review_blob: Pours amber with a small white head.  Nose is butterscotch.  Taste is toasted malt, toffee, and mild hops.  Decent, but nothing that special.
Pours brown, with a small offwhite head.  Nose is caramel.  Taste is sweetish, with notes of spice, nut, malt and caramel.  This grew on me as the beer progressed.  Nice stuff.
Pours reddish brown with a medium fizzy offwhite head.  Nose is malt and bread.  Taste is sweetish, with notes of malt, bread and caramel.  A very nice ESB.

Pours pale gold with an average white, fizzy head.  Nose is malt, grass, and light yeast.  Taste is malt, bread, and minimal hops.  This one is much more malty than most pale lagers.  Decent, refreshing, but nothing spectacular.
Pours amber with a large fizzy offwhite head, fast diminishing.  Nose is malt, caramel.  Taste is sweetish, with notes of roasted malt, spice, raisin, and bread.  A nice bitter.
Pours pale gold with a midsize creamy white head.  Light lacing and carbonization.  Nose is wheat and bread.  Taste is wheat, bread, cinnamon, and orange.  A delightful and refreshing wheat beer.
Pours pale gold with an average sized white, fizzy head.  Nose is skunky.  Taste is mild hops, earth, a hint of honey; basically an average pale lager.
Pours hazy amber with a large creamy white head and good lacing.  Nose is grain and berry.  Taste is berry, spice and medicine.  The flavors didnt mesh for me; not a fan of this one.

Pours red-brown with a large offwhite head and good lacing. Nose is bread and caramel.  Taste has bitterness up front, with notes of dough and earth, sweetness in the finish, with touches of malt, caramel, and honey.  Good, but nothing that screams for me to try it again.
Pours dark brown with an average sized light brown head.  Nose is malt and caramel.  Taste is malt, bread, caramel, and toffee.  A nice beer, very satisfying.

Pours pale golden with a big white head. Nose is malt, grass, and citris.  Taste is malt, hops and straw.  There is a twinge of flavor from the above tastes to give this a shred of character, but not much more beyond that.  Refreshing but unremakable.
Pours clear pale gold, with a big white head.  Nose is hops.  Taste is malt and hops, with a medium level of bitterness for a lager.  Drinkable, but unremarkable.
Pours hazy golden with a big white head. Nose is bready.  Taste is wheat and yeast.  Nice and drinkable, but nothing really remarkable going on here.
Pours pale golden with a big, white pillowy head.  Nose is malt.  Taste is sweet malt up front, with mild hop bitterness in the finish.  Slightly spicy.  Excellent stuff.
Pours pale gold with a big, pillowy, white head.  Head is long lasting with good lacing.  Taste is clean and crisp, with mild hop bitterness.  Very refreshing, excellent stuff.
Pours pale gold with a big white head.  Nose is hop.  Taste is spicy, with notes of malt, banana, sugar and a generous portion of alcohol.  Divine stuff.
Pours amber with a big offwhite head.  Nose is pine.  Taste sweet malt up front, with a great level of bitterness in the finish.  A wonderful IPA.
Pours pale gold with a medium sized white head.  Nose is a little skunky.  Taste is mild hop biiterness.  This is basically not that much different from most macrobrew pale lagers.
Pours dark abmer with an offwhite head.  Nose is malt.  Taste is caramel, toffee, spice and grapefruit upfront.  A little hop bitterness in the finish.  Decent stuff.
Pours reddish copper with a small  offwhite head.  Nose is caramel, yeast.  Taste is sweet up front, with notes of caramel, dough, and spice.  Mild bitterness in the finish. A nice ESB.

Pours hazy amber with a medium white head.  Nose is malt and bread.  Taste is sweet and citris, with notes of peach orange, malt and hop in the finish.  
I would rate this below Samuel Smiths other stuff though this was still nice.
beer_name: Samuel Smiths Organic Best Ale / Organically Produced Ale

review_blob: Pours amber with a big pillowy, uneven white head.  Long lasting head, good lacing.  Nose is caramel.  Taste is malt and caramel with a nice level of bitterness in the aftertaste.  Mouthfeel is a little thin.  A great everyday beer.
Pours reddish brown with a huge offwhite head. Nose is raspberry. Taste is raspberry  and grapefruit. Decent, but unremarkable.
Pours dark amber with a big offwhite head.  Nose is of raisins.  Taste is raisins, chocolate, sugar, and alcohol.  Bitterness in the finish.  Very nice.
Pours reddish copper with a big offwhite head.  Nose is malt and alcohol.  Taste is sweet, with notes of malt. molasses, and alchohol, with bitterness in the finish.  Flavorful and satisfying.
Pours amber with a medium white head.  Nose is yeast and fruit.  Taste is yeast, malt, banana, and alchohol, slightly spicy.  Very nice.

Pours amber with a big white head.  Nose is citris and malt.  Taste is pine hops and malt.  For an IPA this is really weak on the bitterness level, more like a pale ale.  Smooth and drinkable, but if youre in the mood for the IPA style you might be disappointed.
Pours cloudy orangish gold with a long lasting, uneven white head.  Nose is banana and wheat.  Taste is sweet and spicy, with notes of wheat  and banana.  This is a delightful hefeweizen.
Pours pale gold with a white uneven head.  Nose is grassy.  Taste is sweet malt up front, with mild hop bitterness in the finish.  Nothing spectacular, but a good pils.
Pours brown with a big offwhite head. Nose is fruity,  spicy.  Taste is spicy and sweet, with notes of brown sugar and caramel.  Character doesnt bowl you over, yet is very solid. Enjoyable stuff.

Pours amber, somewhat cloudy with a small, white, fast diminishing head.  Nose is grapefruit.  Taste is spicy and citris up front, with a good level of hop bitterness in the finish.  This is well balanced and very smooth.  A great IPA.
Pours cloudy brown with an offwhite fizzy head.  Nose is wheat.  Taste is spicy and sweet, with notes of cinnamon and caramel.  A nice dunkelweizen.
Pours amber with a small white head.  Nose is malt.  Taste is malt and caramel, with a hint of spice.  Not bad, not great, but drinkable.

Pours cloudy pale gold with a nice white uneaven head.  Nose is bready.  Taste is sweet and spicy, with notes of cinnamon, banana, wheat and bisquit.  Crisp and refreshing, this beer is really delightful.
Pours pale gold and cloudy with a white head.  Nose is bready.  Taste upfront is bisquit and wheat, with a faint tart citris taste in the finish. Not spectacular, but crisp, smooth, and refreshing.
Pours amber with a decent white head.  Nose is malt. Taste is subdued, with notes of malt, caramel, and citris. Mouthfeel is light; overall this is crisp and refreshing.  A good summer beer.
Pours brownish with a good sized white head.  Lots of carbonization.  Nose is sweet caramel.  Taste is spicy, with notes of sugar, malt, and nuts.  This is smooth and crisp.  A delightful experience.
Pours reddish with a pinkish, big, fizzy head.  Nose is cherries and cough syrup.  Taste is sweet cherries up front, with a tartness in the finish.  Memorable and enjoyable.

Pours reddish brown with a big, white pillowy, uneaven head.  Nose is fruity.  Taste is spicy, with notes of cinnamon, caramel and bubblegum.  Extremely flavorful and complex.  The sweetness dances toward cloying without quite crossing the line.  Interesting and memorable.

Pales pale golden with a big white head.  Good lacing.  Nose is faint but crisp and grassy.  Taste is a hint of sweet malt up front , followed by hops in the finish.  Overall this is crisp, smooth, and refreshing, if not terribly complicated.  Good stuff.
